AFRICAN HORSE SICKNESS - SOUTH AFRICA (WESTERN CAPE): OIE
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Sat 24 Mar 2007
From: ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, WAHID [World Animal Health
Information Database], weekly disease information, 2007; 20(13) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>

African horse sickness, South Africa
------------------------------------
Information received on (and dated) 23 Mar 2007, from Mr Bothle
Michael Modisane, Assistant Director General, Department of
Agriculture, National Regulatory Services, Pretoria, South Africa
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Start date: 15 Mar 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 22 Mar 2007
Report date: 23 Mar 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 23 Mar 2007
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 17 Mar 2004
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: orbivirus
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: defined zone within the country
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak location: Kunnenburg, Paarl (Western Cape Province)
Date of start of outbreak: 15 Mar 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Species: equidae
Susceptible: 18
Cases: 1
Deaths: 1
Destroyed: 0
Slaughtered: 0
Outbreak statistics
Species: equidae
Apparent morbidity rate: 5.56 percent
Apparent mortality rate: 5.56 percent
Apparent case fatality rate: 100 percent
Proportion susceptible removed*: 5.56 percent
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death,
destruction, or slaughter
Epidemiology
Source of infection: unknown or inconclusive. Vectors
Epidemiological comments: the outbreak occurred in the African Horse
Sickness (AHS) Surveillance Zone of the Western Cape Province (WCP).
The last reported outbreak in the AHS Surveillance Zone of the ECP
[Eastern Cape Province- Mod. PC] ended on 17 Mar 2004.
Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute (OIE's
Reference Laboratory)
Species: equidae
Test: nested RT-PCR (reverse transcription polymerase chain reaction)
Test date: 22 Mar 2007
Result: positive
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of the outbreak area can be seen in the full report referenced above.
The previous OIE report [8 May 2006] on the occurrence of African
horse sickness (AHS) in the Western Cape province can be seen at
<http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_19.HTM#Sec9>. That outbreak
was in the protected zone for AHS and involved 4 farms with 15 cases
and 6 deaths out of 383 susceptible horses. - Mod.PC]
